<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/2003</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-13T20:00:00+08:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your telegram September 9, 6 p.m. The conclusion of a loan in
                                connection with the scheme of currency notes is denied by the
                                Minister of Finance but the truth of the matter is nevertheless in
                                doubt.</p>
                            <p>So far as can be learned the enforcement of the gold regulations is
                                in abeyance for time being but while the ultimate intentions of the
                                authorities cannot be known, it is not supposed that they have
                                definitely abandoned the project.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>